The paper deals with the problem of designing optimal control policies for scheduling packet transmissions in a stochastic wireless network. This involves the study of queueing systems, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also involves the use of optimization techniques, which are studied in the sub-categories of Mathematical Optimization (cs.MA) and Game Theory (cs.GT). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
